  "local_port": 50944,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I remove certain questions/answers from my feed?",
  "response": "Removing specific questions or answers from your feed can enhance your browsing experience by tailoring the content to your preferences. The exact steps to achieve this depend on the platform you're using. Below are general guidelines for several popular platforms:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Social Media Platforms**\n\n#### **a. Facebook**\n\n- **Unfollow or Hide Posts:**\n  - **From a Person/Page:** Go to the profile of the person or page, click the \"Following\" button, and select \"Unfollow\" to stop seeing their posts in your feed.\n  - **Individual Posts:** Click the three dots (`...`) on a specific post and select \"Hide post\" or \"Snooze [Person/Page] for 30 days.\"\n\n- **Customize News Feed Preferences:**\n  - Go to **Settings & Privacy > Settings > News Feed Preferences** to prioritize, unfollow, or reconnect with people and pages.\n\n#### **b. Twitter**\n\n- **Mute or Block Users:**\n  - Visit the profile you want to mute or block.\n  - Click the three dots (`...`) and choose \"Mute\" or \"Block.\"\n\n- **Mute Keywords:**\n  - Go to **Settings and Privacy > Privacy and Safety > Mute and block > Muted words** to add specific words or phrases you want to hide from your timeline.\n\n#### **c. Instagram**\n\n- **Mute Users:**\n  - Visit the profile you want to mute.\n  - Tap \"Following,\" then select \"Mute\" and choose whether to mute posts, stories, or both.\n\n- **Hide Specific Posts:**\n  - While you can't hide individual posts directly, you can unfollow accounts or use the \"Not Interested\" option on IGTV and Reels.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Reddit**\n\n- **Unsubscribe from Subreddits:**\n  - Navigate to the subreddit you want to unsubscribe from.\n  - Click \"Joined\" to leave the subreddit.\n\n- **Filter Out Content:**\n  - Use the **block** feature to hide posts containing specific keywords.\n  - Install browser extensions like **Reddit Enhancement Suite (RES)** to customize your feed further.\n\n- **Hide Specific Posts:**\n  - Click the three dots (`...`) below a post and select \"Hide.\"\n\n---\n\n### **3. Stack Exchange (e.g., Stack Overflow)**\n\n- **Ignore Tags:**\n  - Go to your profile by clicking your avatar.\n  - Navigate to **Preferences** or **Tags**.\n  - Add tags you want to ignore, which will gray out or hide questions with those tags.\n\n- **Favorite Tags:**\n  - Conversely, adding favorite tags can help prioritize certain topics in your feed.\n\n- **Custom Filters:**\n  - Use the **custom filter** option to show or hide questions based on specific criteria.\n\n---\n\n### **4. YouTube**\n\n- **Hide Specific Channels:**\n  - Click the three dots (`...`) next to a video from the channel you want to hide.\n  - Select \"Don't recommend channel.\"\n\n- **Use \"Not Interested\":**\n  - On videos you don't like, click the three dots and choose \"Not interested\" to refine recommendations.\n\n- **Manage Watch History:**\n  - Clearing or pausing your watch history can reset and improve future recommendations.\n\n---\n\n### **5. News Aggregators (e.g., Feedly, Flipboard)**\n\n- **Unsubscribe from Sources:**\n  - Remove feeds from sources that consistently provide unwanted content.\n\n- **Use Keyword Filters:**\n  - Set up filters to exclude articles containing specific keywords or topics.\n\n- **Customize Categories:**\n  - Organize your feeds into categories and prioritize those that align with your interests.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Email Newsletters and Subscriptions**\n\n- **Unsubscribe:**\n  - At the bottom of most emails, there's an \"Unsubscribe\" link. Click it to stop receiving future emails.\n\n- **Email Filters:**\n  - Set up rules in your email client to automatically move, archive, or delete emails containing specific keywords or from certain senders.\n\n---\n\n### **7. General Tips Across Platforms**\n\n- **Adjust Notification Settings:**\n  - Explore the settings or preferences section of the platform to manage what types of content you receive.\n\n- **Use Browser Extensions:**\n  - Extensions like **AdBlock**, **uBlock Origin**, or **Content Blockers** can help filter unwanted content across various websites.\n\n- **Report Inappropriate Content:**\n  - Utilize the platform's reporting features to flag content that violates community guidelines, which may lead to its removal.\n\n- **Create Lists or Groups:**\n  - Some platforms allow you to organize content into lists or groups, letting you focus on preferred content sources.\n\n---\n\nIf you have a specific platform in mind that isn't covered above, please provide more details, and I can offer more tailored instructions.",
